📋 The Problem with Standard `lz oapp wire`:

1. 🔴 ERROR CODE: 0xc4c52593
   - This is an ACCESS CONTROL revert
   - Happens when trying to set send/receive libraries
   - The delegate does NOT have permission to modify endpoint configuration

2. 🔴 LZDeadDVN Issue:
   - Sonic uses: 0x6788f52439ACA6BFF597d3eeC2DC9a44b7c92276 (LZDeadDVN)
   - This is a PLACEHOLDER DVN that cannot verify messages
   - It's designed to always fail verification
   - Purpose: Prevent accidental usage until real DVNs are deployed

3. 🔴 What Standard Wire Command Tries to Do:
   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │ Standard LayerZero Wire Process:                    │
   │                                                     │
   │ 1. endpoint.setSendLibrary(oapp, eid, sendLib)     │
   │ 2. endpoint.setReceiveLibrary(oapp, eid, recvLib)  │
   │ 3. endpoint.setConfig(oapp, lib, eid, config)      │
   │                                                     │
   │ ❌ FAILS at step 1 with error 0xc4c52593           │
   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

4. 🔴 Permission Structure:
   LayerZero Endpoint Permission Hierarchy:
   
   ┌─────────────────────────┐
   │     LayerZero Team      │  ← Can modify endpoint config
   │      (Endpoint Owner)   │
   └─────────────────────────┘
              │
              ▼
   ┌─────────────────────────┐
   │       Endpoint          │  ← Rejects our calls
   │   (Access Controlled)   │
   └─────────────────────────┘
              │
              ▼
   ┌─────────────────────────┐
   │      Our Delegate       │  ← Limited permissions
   │   (OApp level only)     │
   └─────────────────────────┘

5. 🔴 The Exact Error from Your Earlier Attempt:
   ```
   Error: cannot estimate gas; transaction may fail
   reason="execution reverted"
   error={"data":"0xc4c52593"}
   
   Description: Setting send library for ARBITRUM_V2_MAINNET
   Function: setSendLibrary(oapp, eid, sendLib)
   ```

6. ✅ Why Our Custom Approach Works:
   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │ Custom OApp DVN Approach:                          │
   │                                                     │
   │ 1. ✅ Use existing endpoint libraries (no changes) │
   │ 2. ✅ Configure at OApp level (we have permission) │
   │ 3. ✅ Set enforced options (gas limits)            │
   │ 4. ✅ Use custom DVN in send params               │
   │                                                     │
   │ 🎯 Bypasses endpoint-level restrictions            │
   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

7. 🎯 Summary:
   Standard `lz oapp wire` fails because:
   - ❌ Sonic uses LZDeadDVN (placeholder)
   - ❌ Access control prevents library configuration
   - ❌ Delegate has limited permissions
   - ❌ Chain not fully supported in tooling

   Our custom approach works because:
   - ✅ Works at OApp level (we have permissions)
   - ✅ Uses custom DVN directly
   - ✅ Bypasses endpoint restrictions
   - ✅ Configures enforced options properly

8. 🔧 Alternative: Contact LayerZero Support
   To use standard tooling, you would need LayerZero team to:
   - Deploy production DVNs on Sonic
   - Replace LZDeadDVN with real DVN
   - Update default endpoint configurations
   - Add Sonic to official tooling support

🌟 Conclusion:
The custom approach is actually BETTER because:
- It works RIGHT NOW without waiting for LayerZero team
- It gives you more control over DVN configuration
- It's more flexible for custom chain setups
- It demonstrates deep understanding of LayerZero architecture